<!--{
    "title":       "@this",
    "out":         "tags-this.html",
    "description": "What does the <code>this</code> keyword refer to here?"
}-->
<h3>Syntax</h3>
<code>@this &lt;namePath&gt;</code>

<h3>Overview</h3>

<p>The @this tag tells the parser what the <code>this</code> keyword is referring to.
This is useful in cases where JSDoc would not properly work it out otherwise.
</p>

<h3>Examples</h3>

{{#example}}
/** @constructor */
function Foo(name) {
    setName.apply(this, name);
}

/** @this Foo */
function setName(name) {
    /** document me */
    this.name = name;
}
{{/example}}

<p>In the example above, <code>this.name</code> from the <code>setName</code> function is documented as <code>Foo#name</code>.
Without the @this tag, a global symbol "name" would have been documented instead.
</p>

